Defendant in custody.
The defendant is sentenced to the Manitowoc County Jail for thirty-four (34) months.  That is sixteen (16) months initial confinement followed by eighteen (18) months extended supervision.
The Court finds the defendant eligible for both the Challenge Incarceration Program and the Substance Abuse Program.
The defendant has credit for 134 days.
Conditions of extended supervision:
1) Assessment, treatment, counseling as deemed appropriate by the Departments assessment process;
2) AODA assessment and follow through;
3) Maintain fulltime employment or work search;
4) Submit to random urine screens and pay for same;
5) Pay a $500.00 fine plus costs, including $100.00 buy money to Metro Drug Unit, for a total of 1,705.50;
6) Have no contact with Kevin Karl;
7) pay supervision fees in an amount to be determined by DOC.
Minutes.

The State files an Amended Information which charges a single count of possess Methamphetamine, contrary to Section 961.41(eg)(g) of the Wisconsin Statutes.  
NO CONTEST plea entered to the amended charge.  Convicted.
Sentence is withheld and the defendant is placed on probation to DOC for three (3) years.
Conditions of probation:
1) assessment, treatment, counseling as deemed appropriate by the Department's assessment process;
2) AODA assessment and follow through;
3) maintain fulltime employment or job search;
4) submit to random urine screens and pay for same;
5) reimburse Metro Drug Unit for $100.00 buy money;
6) pay $500.00 fine plus costs, total of $1,605.00;
7) spend six (6) months in the county jail, under the Huber Law, stayed and to be imposed at the agent's discretion and upon order of the court;
8) have no contact with Kevin Karl;
9) pay supervision fees in an amount to be determined by DOC.
Amended Information.
Plea Questionnaire and Waiver of Rights.
Notice of Right to Seek Postconviction Relief.
